-- Australia shares set for breather after last week's rally
-- By Swati Pandey
-- Sun Dec 21, 2014 05:59PM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 22 (Reuters) - Australian stocks could take a bit of a breather on Monday following a strong rebound late last week, with trading likely to be thin in a holiday-shortened week.

Stock index futures <YAPcm1> edged up 0.3 percent to 5,329, a small discount to the underlying S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO.> The benchmark surged 2.5 percent on Friday, the biggest one-day gain since July 2013. Transfield <TSE.AX> shares will be in focus after Spanish infrastructure group Ferrovial <FER.MC> raised its full takeover offer for the Australian company. [ID:nL3N0U50J4] New Zealand's benchmark NZX 50 index <.NZ50> was mostly unchanged in early deals on Monday. For a summary of overnight action across global markets, double click on [AU/CALL]